## Description {#details}

This file implements a set that has insertion order iteration characteristics.

This is useful for keeping a set of things that need to be visited later but in a deterministic order (insertion order). The interface is purposefully minimal.

This file defines SetVector and SmallSetVector, which performs no allocations if the SetVector has less than a certain number of elements.

<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A vector that has set insertion semantics.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This adapter class provides a way to keep a set of things that also has the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// property of a deterministic iteration order. The order of iteration is the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// order of insertion.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The key and value types are derived from the Set and Vector types</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// respectively. This allows the vector-type operations and set-type operations</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to have different types. In particular, this is useful when storing pointers</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">/// as &quot;Foo &#42;&quot; values but looking them up as &quot;const Foo &#42;&quot; keys.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// No constraint is placed on the key and value types, although it is assumed</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that value&#95;type can be converted into key&#95;type for insertion. Users must be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">/// aware of any loss of information in this conversion. For example, setting</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">/// value&#95;type to float and key&#95;type to int can produce very surprising results,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// but it is not explicitly disallowed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
